{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Our ablation experiments highlighted the crucial roles of DCN and LOPE strategy in enhancing model performance.",
    "While numerous models have been proposed for computer, molecular, and materials fields, their performance often deteriorates when transferred to the crystal materials domain.",
    "To validate the effectiveness and generality of the DCN and LOPE strategy, we fused DCN and LOPE strategy into representative models from these three fields.",
    "We selected GraphSAGE 47, GAT 48, and GIN 49 for the computer domain; AttentiveFP 50, PAiNN 51, and HamNet 52 for the molecular domain; and CGCNN, MEGNet, and Schnet for the materials domain.",
    "These models cover spatial convolutions, message passing, 3D geometric message passing, attention mechanisms, and graph transformers, among others, in the realm of GNNs."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "We selected GraphSAGE 47, GAT 48, and GIN 49 for the computer domain; AttentiveFP 50, PAiNN 51, and HamNet 52 for the molecular domain; and CGCNN, MEGNet, and Schnet for the materials domain."
